<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,839,1202]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,877,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
Due to the similar shape of the palp and dorsum, III/IV-L- 
<number box="[1033,1072,877,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
with numerous pinnate dorsal setae and sclerotized excretory pore, 
<taxonomicName box="[595,826,914,939]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis box="[595,826,914,939]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Sperchon amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1178,914,939]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis box="[960,1178,914,939]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Sperchon hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[198,307,952,978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[351,501,952,977]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis box="[351,501,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, shows that it agrees in all important diagnostic features with 
<taxonomicName box="[1292,1428,952,977]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis box="[1292,1428,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName box="[281,421,989,1014]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amuzgari">
<emphasis box="[281,421,989,1014]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. amuzgari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is synonymized here with 
<taxonomicName box="[736,863,989,1014]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis box="[736,863,989,1014]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
